          <h2>HHS STEM Academy Collaboration</h2>
          <p>This project also serves as an opportunity to engage the academic community around James Madison University by providing local area high school students the opportunity to participate in ‘Citizen Science’. This initiative was undertaken on the part of Dr. Stockwell in partnership with Mr. Myron Blosser of the HHS STEM Academy. By learning soil collection and microbe isolation techniques, these high school students’ contributions of microbial isolations will help the researchers’ genomic library grow while having an opportunity to learn new skills and become exposed to real scientific field work.</p>
          <p>This presents a powerful learning experience, a rare opportunity to participate in college-level research and the potential to inspire students to pursue education and/or careers in biotechnology. This symbiotic relationship between college and high school students embodies a critical focus of the ISAT program; solving real world problems by integrating research, teaching and collaboration.</p>
          <p>Because the HHS STEM students can focus their efforts on soil sample collection, seed inoculations and plant harvesting; the ISAT researchers can take a more complete ownership of their project by allowing them to delve in, and devote more time to, more complex genetic analyses. In addition, there is a real opportunity for the senior capstone students to receive practice, and become comfortable with, service based learning. This can come in the form of creating lab protocols to guide the citizen scientists in their sample collection and verification, producing interactive video demonstrations that provide an in-depth look at some of the advanced equipment and techniques being used in the JMU Sciences Program. Given the ambitious plans for expansion of research, including Citizen Science outreach, there is the potential for an exponential increase in interest and participation in this research program on the part of senior capstone researchers.</p>
